    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect TX request handling when SFN/SF wraps around\n\n### Summary\nThe `pnf_handle_tx_request` function in the PNF P7 processing was incorrectly rejecting valid TX requests that fell within the timing window but occurred after an SFN/SF wraparound. This caused TX requests near the end of the SFN/SF space (e.g., SFN 1023, SF 9) to be treated as out-of-window when they were actually valid.\n\nThis fix corrects the wraparound logic in `is_p7_request_in_window` to properly accept requests that are within the timing window even when they span the SFN/SF boundary.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/pnf/src/pnf_p7.c`: Fixed the wraparound condition check in `is_p7_request_in_window` function to correctly identify in-window requests that span the SFN/SF boundary.\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Configure a PNF with a small subframe buffer size (e.g., 5)\n2. Send a TX request with SFN/SF near the end of the space (e.g., 10239 for SFN 1023, SF 9)\n3. Send another TX request that should be within the window but wraps around (e.g., SFN 0, SF 1)\n4. Observe that the second request is incorrectly rejected with a \"late\" message\n\nAfter applying the fix, the second request should be correctly accepted and processed.\n"
}